<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-06T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-06T16:00:00-05:00" n="963" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d963">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3057.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American Consul at
                                    Chihuahua</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-06T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 6, 1912—4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your March 5. The Embassy, in advising Americans to leave Chihuahua, is
                            acting upon information from your Consulate as to conditions in your
                            district, and must, from the very nature of the case, therefore, depend
                            upon your discretion both as to the necessity of warning Americans to
                            leave particular localities and the means of conveying this warning to
                            them.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>